{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":847,"text":"When the Portuguese arrived\nin Latin America about 500 years ago,"},{"time":5818,"text":"they obviously found\nthis amazing tropical forest."},{"time":8928,"text":"And among all this biodiversity\nthat they had never seen before,"},{"time":13165,"text":"they found one species that caught\ntheir attention very quickly."},{"time":17335,"text":"This species, when you cut the bark,\nyou find a very dark red resin"},{"time":23580,"text":"that was very good to paint\nand dye fabric to make clothes."},{"time":29354,"text":"The indigenous people called\nthis species pau brasil,"},{"time":33799,"text":"and that's the reason why this land became\n\"land of Brasil,\" and later on, Brazil."},{"time":39820,"text":"That's the only country in the world\nthat has the name of a tree."},{"time":44356,"text":"So you can imagine that it's very cool\nto be a forester in Brazil,"},{"time":49560,"text":"among other reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51507,"text":"Forest products are all around us."},{"time":54393,"text":"Apart from all those products,"},{"time":56326,"text":"the forest is very important\nfor climate regulation."},{"time":60219,"text":"In Brazil, almost 70 percent\nof the evaporation that makes rain"},{"time":65453,"text":"actually comes from the forest."},{"time":67894,"text":"Just the Amazon pumps to the atmosphere\n20 billion tons of water every day."},{"time":76984,"text":"This is more than what the Amazon River,\nwhich is the largest river in the world,"},{"time":81456,"text":"puts in the sea per day,\nwhich is 17 billion tons."},{"time":86116,"text":"If we had to boil water to get\nthe same effect as evapotranspiration,"},{"time":91215,"text":"we would need six months of the entire\npower generation capacity of the world."},{"time":97722,"text":"So it's a hell of a service for all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":100980,"text":"We have in the world\nabout four billion hectares of forests."},{"time":104595,"text":"This is more or less China, U.S.,\nCanada and Brazil all together,"},{"time":110232,"text":"in terms of size, to have an idea."},{"time":112536,"text":"Three quarters of that\nis in the temperate zone,"},{"time":116646,"text":"and just one quarter is in the tropics,"},{"time":120009,"text":"but this one quarter, one billion\nhectares, holds most of the biodiversity,"},{"time":126023,"text":"and very importantly, 50 percent\nof the living biomass, the carbon."},{"time":132193,"text":"Now, we used to have\nsix billion hectares of forest --"},{"time":136229,"text":"50 percent more than\nwhat we have -- 2,000 years ago."},{"time":140072,"text":"We've actually lost two billion hectares\nin the last 2,000 years."},{"time":143638,"text":"But in the last 100 years,\nwe lost half of that."},{"time":147915,"text":"That was when we shifted\nfrom deforestation of temperate forests"},{"time":152614,"text":"to deforestation of tropical forests."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156067,"text":"So think of this: In 100 years,"},{"time":159439,"text":"we lost the same amount\nof forest in the tropics"},{"time":163275,"text":"that we lost in 2,000 years\nin temperate forests."},{"time":166916,"text":"That's the speed of the destruction\nthat we are having."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170819,"text":"Now, Brazil is an important\npiece of this puzzle."},{"time":174895,"text":"We have the second largest\nforest in the world, just after Russia."},{"time":178655,"text":"It means 12 percent of all\nthe world's forests are in Brazil,"},{"time":182341,"text":"most of that in the Amazon."},{"time":184153,"text":"It's the largest piece of forest we have.\nIt's a very big, large area."},{"time":187597,"text":"You can see that you could fit\nmany of the European countries there."},{"time":190979,"text":"We still have 80 percent\nof the forest cover."},{"time":194482,"text":"That's the good news."},{"time":196111,"text":"But we lost 15 percent in just 30 years."},{"time":200818,"text":"So if you go with that speed,"},{"time":202706,"text":"very soon, we will loose this powerful\npump that we have in the Amazon"},{"time":207745,"text":"that regulates our climate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210010,"text":"Deforestation was growing\nfast and accelerating"},{"time":212873,"text":"at the end of the '90s\nand the beginning of the 2000s."},{"time":215714,"text":"(Chainsaw sound)"},{"time":219641,"text":"(Sound of falling tree)"},{"time":223598,"text":"Twenty-seven thousand\nsquare kilometers in one year."},{"time":227947,"text":"This is 2.7 million hectares."},{"time":231602,"text":"It's almost like half\nof Costa Rica every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237654,"text":"So at this moment -- this is 2003, 2004 --"},{"time":241639,"text":"I happened to be coming to work\nin the government."},{"time":246116,"text":"And together with other teammates\nin the National Forest Department,"},{"time":250566,"text":"we were assigned a task to join a team\nand find out the causes of deforestation,"},{"time":256293,"text":"and make a plan to combat that\nat a national level,"},{"time":259005,"text":"involving the local governments,\nthe civil society,"},{"time":262341,"text":"business, local communities,"},{"time":264184,"text":"in an effort that could\ntackle those causes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267217,"text":"So we came up with this plan\nwith 144 actions in different areas."},{"time":273019,"text":"Now I will go through\nall of them one by one --"},{"time":275366,"text":"no, just giving some examples\nof what we had done in the next few years."},{"time":282170,"text":"So the first thing, we set up a system\nwith the national space agency"},{"time":287896,"text":"that could actually see\nwhere deforestation is happening,"},{"time":290903,"text":"almost in real time."},{"time":292404,"text":"So now in Brazil, \nwe have this system, DETER,"},{"time":294788,"text":"where every month,\nor every two months,"},{"time":298083,"text":"we get information on\nwhere deforestation is happening"},{"time":300867,"text":"so we can actually act\nwhen it's happening."},{"time":303735,"text":"And all the information\nis fully transparent"},{"time":305878,"text":"so others can replicate that\nin independent systems."},{"time":308862,"text":"This allows us, among other things,"},{"time":310841,"text":"to apprehend 1.4 million cubic meters\nof logs that were illegally taken."},{"time":317452,"text":"Part of that we saw and sell,\nand all the revenue becomes a fund"},{"time":323067,"text":"that now funds conservation projects\nof local communities as an endowment fund."},{"time":328755,"text":"This also allows us\nto make a big operation"},{"time":331189,"text":"to seize corruption and illegal activities"},{"time":333914,"text":"that ended up having 700 people in prison,\nincluding a lot of public servants."},{"time":340120,"text":"Then we made the connection\nthat areas that have been doing"},{"time":344172,"text":"illegal deforestation should not get\nany kind of credit or finance."},{"time":348525,"text":"So we cut this through the bank system\nand then linked this to the end users."},{"time":353037,"text":"So supermarkets,\nthe slaughterhouses, and so on"},{"time":355442,"text":"that buy products\nfrom illegal clear-cut areas,"},{"time":358868,"text":"they also can be liable\nfor the deforestation."},{"time":362526,"text":"So making all these connections to help\nto push the problem down."},{"time":366110,"text":"And also we work a lot\non land tenure issues."},{"time":369503,"text":"It's very important for conflicts."},{"time":371701,"text":"Fifty million hectares\nof protected areas were created,"},{"time":374707,"text":"which is an area the size of Spain."},{"time":380496,"text":"And of those, eight million\nwere indigenous lands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384743,"text":"Now we start to see results."},{"time":388429,"text":"So in the last 10 years,"},{"time":390928,"text":"deforestation came down\nin Brazil 75 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394532,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":400143,"text":"So if we compare it\nwith the average deforestation"},{"time":403915,"text":"that we had in the last decade,"},{"time":406177,"text":"we saved 8.7 million hectares,\nwhich is the size of Austria."},{"time":411181,"text":"But more importantly,\nit avoided the emission"},{"time":413694,"text":"of three billion tons\nof CO2 in the atmosphere."},{"time":416579,"text":"This is by far the largest contribution\nto reduce greenhouse gas emissions,"},{"time":421653,"text":"until today, as a positive action."},{"time":425727,"text":"One may think that when you do\nthese kinds of actions"},{"time":428908,"text":"to decrease, to push down deforestation,"},{"time":432037,"text":"you will have an economic impact"},{"time":434135,"text":"because you will not have\neconomic activity or something like that."},{"time":438297,"text":"But it's interesting to know\nthat it's quite the opposite."},{"time":441084,"text":"In fact, in the period when we have\nthe deepest decline of deforestation,"},{"time":445959,"text":"the economy grew, on average,\ndouble from the previous decade,"},{"time":450108,"text":"when deforestation was actually going up."},{"time":452697,"text":"So it's a good lesson for us."},{"time":454752,"text":"Maybe this is completely disconnected,"},{"time":457100,"text":"as we just learned by having\ndeforestation come down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461167,"text":"Now this is all good news,\nand it's quite an achievement,"},{"time":465120,"text":"and we obviously should be\nvery proud about that."},{"time":468448,"text":"But it's not even close to sufficient."},{"time":471219,"text":"In fact, if you think about\nthe deforestation in the Amazon in 2013,"},{"time":476109,"text":"that was over half a million hectares,"},{"time":479748,"text":"which means that every minute,"},{"time":482412,"text":"an area the size of two soccer fields"},{"time":485785,"text":"is being cut in the Amazon\nlast year, just last year."},{"time":489665,"text":"If we sum up the deforestation we have\nin the other biomes in Brazil,"},{"time":493748,"text":"we are talking about still the largest\ndeforestation rate in the world."},{"time":499114,"text":"It's more or less like\nwe are forest heroes,"},{"time":502459,"text":"but still deforestation champions."},{"time":505629,"text":"So we can't be satisfied,\nnot even close to satisfied."},{"time":510327,"text":"So the next step, I think,"},{"time":512136,"text":"is to fight to have zero loss\nof forest cover in Brazil"},{"time":516687,"text":"and to have that as a goal for 2020."},{"time":520062,"text":"That's our next step."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521422,"text":"Now I've always been interested\nin the relationship"},{"time":524407,"text":"between climate change and forests."},{"time":526431,"text":"First, because 15 percent of greenhouse\ngas emissions come from deforestation,"},{"time":532182,"text":"so it's a big part of the problem."},{"time":534454,"text":"But also, forests can be\na big part of the solution"},{"time":537570,"text":"since that's the best way we know\nto sink, capture and store carbon."},{"time":544694,"text":"Now, there is another relationship\nof climate and forests"},{"time":547487,"text":"that really stuck me in 2008\nand made me change my career"},{"time":551553,"text":"from forests to working\nwith climate change."},{"time":555039,"text":"I went to visit Canada,\nin British Columbia,"},{"time":557724,"text":"together with the chiefs of\nthe forest services of other countries"},{"time":562738,"text":"that we have a kind of alliance of them,\nlike Canada, Russia, India, China, U.S."},{"time":569143,"text":"And when we were there\nwe learned about this pine beetle"},{"time":574257,"text":"that is literally eating\nthe forests in Canada."},{"time":577547,"text":"What we see here, those brown trees,\nthese are really dead trees."},{"time":583819,"text":"They are standing dead trees\nbecause of the larvae of the beetle."},{"time":588384,"text":"What happens is that this beetle"},{"time":591429,"text":"is controlled by\nthe cold weather in the winter."},{"time":594229,"text":"For many years now, they don't have\nthe sufficient cold weather"},{"time":597980,"text":"to actually control\nthe population of this beetle."},{"time":601042,"text":"And it became a disease\nthat is really killing billions of trees."},{"time":608284,"text":"So I came back with this notion\nthat the forest is actually"},{"time":612574,"text":"one of the earliest and most affected\nvictims of climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617843,"text":"So I was thinking,"},{"time":619503,"text":"if I succeed in working\nwith all my colleagues"},{"time":623967,"text":"to actually help to stop deforestation,"},{"time":626443,"text":"maybe we will lose the battle\nlater on for climate change"},{"time":630690,"text":"by floods, heat, fires and so on."},{"time":634630,"text":"So I decided to leave the forest service"},{"time":638011,"text":"and start to work directly\non climate change,"},{"time":641415,"text":"find a way to think and understand\nthe challenge, and go from there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645463,"text":"Now, the challenge of climate change\nis pretty straightforward."},{"time":650051,"text":"The goal is very clear."},{"time":651819,"text":"We want to limit the increase\nof the average temperature"},{"time":655428,"text":"of the planet to two degrees."},{"time":658001,"text":"There are several reasons for that."},{"time":659737,"text":"I will not get into that now."},{"time":661984,"text":"But in order to get\nto this limit of two degrees,"},{"time":665441,"text":"which is possible for us to survive,"},{"time":669254,"text":"the IPCC, the Intergovernmental\nPanel on Climate Change,"},{"time":674317,"text":"defines that we have a budget of emissions\nof 1,000 billion tons of CO2"},{"time":681337,"text":"from now until the end of the century."},{"time":684579,"text":"So if we divide this\nby the number of years,"},{"time":687243,"text":"what we have is an average budget\nof 11 billion tons of CO2 per year."},{"time":693910,"text":"Now what is one ton of CO2?"},{"time":696118,"text":"It's more or less what one small car,\nrunning 20 kilometers a day,"},{"time":702107,"text":"will emit in one year."},{"time":704644,"text":"Or it's one flight, one way,"},{"time":706705,"text":"from São Paulo to Johannesburg\nor to London, one way."},{"time":710089,"text":"Two ways, two tons."},{"time":711928,"text":"So 11 billion tons is twice that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715402,"text":"Now the emissions today\nare 50 billion tons, and it's growing."},{"time":722467,"text":"It's growing and maybe\nit will be 61 by 2020."},{"time":726895,"text":"Now we need to go down to 10 by 2050."},{"time":731592,"text":"And while this happens,"},{"time":733367,"text":"the population will grow\nfrom seven to nine billion people,"},{"time":736514,"text":"the economy will grow\nfrom 60 trillion dollars in 2010"},{"time":739412,"text":"to 200 trillion dollars."},{"time":741474,"text":"And so what we need to do\nis to be much more efficient"},{"time":745484,"text":"in a way that we can go\nfrom seven tons of carbon per capita"},{"time":750425,"text":"per person, per year,\ninto something like one."},{"time":755307,"text":"You have to choose.\nYou take the airplane or you have a car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760338,"text":"So the question is, can we make it?"},{"time":762986,"text":"And that's the exactly the same question"},{"time":764903,"text":"I got when I was developing\na plan to combat deforestation."},{"time":769048,"text":"It's such a big problem, so complex.\nCan we really do it?"},{"time":773677,"text":"I think so. Think of this:"},{"time":776366,"text":"Deforestation means 60 percent\nof the greenhouse gas emissions"},{"time":781677,"text":"in Brazil in the last decade."},{"time":783516,"text":"Now it's a little bit\nless than 30 percent."},{"time":785587,"text":"In the world, 60 percent is energy."},{"time":789487,"text":"So if we can tackle directly the energy,"},{"time":793026,"text":"the same way we could\ntackle deforestation,"},{"time":795714,"text":"maybe we can have a chance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797890,"text":"So there are five things\nthat I think we should do."},{"time":801547,"text":"First, we need to disconnect development\nfrom carbon emissions."},{"time":805893,"text":"We don't need to clear-cut all the forests\nto actually get more jobs"},{"time":811982,"text":"and agriculture and have more economy."},{"time":813795,"text":"That's what we proved\nwhen we decreased deforestation"},{"time":816297,"text":"and the economy continued to grow."},{"time":818113,"text":"Same thing could happen\nin the energy sector."},{"time":822510,"text":"Second, we have to move\nthe incentives to the right place."},{"time":825793,"text":"Today, 500 billion dollars a year\ngoes into subsidies for fossil fuels."},{"time":831050,"text":"Why don't we put a price on carbon\nand transfer this to the renewable energy?"},{"time":836204,"text":"Third, we need to measure\nand make it transparent"},{"time":839638,"text":"where, when and who\nis emitting greenhouse gases"},{"time":842932,"text":"so we can have actions specifically\nfor each one of those opportunities."},{"time":847128,"text":"Fourth, we need to leapfrog\nthe routes of development,"},{"time":851914,"text":"which means, you don't need\nto go to the landline telephone"},{"time":854710,"text":"before you get to the mobile phones."},{"time":857044,"text":"Same way we don't need\nto go to fossil fuels"},{"time":859182,"text":"to the one billion people\nwho don't have access to energy"},{"time":861890,"text":"before we get to the clean energy."},{"time":864084,"text":"And fifth and last,"},{"time":865970,"text":"we need to share responsibility\nbetween governments,"},{"time":868668,"text":"business and civil society."},{"time":871390,"text":"There is work to do for everybody,\nand we need to have everybody on board."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876309,"text":"So to finalize,"},{"time":877651,"text":"I think the future is not like a fate"},{"time":881371,"text":"that you have to just go\nas business as usual goes."},{"time":884109,"text":"We need to have the courage\nto actually change the route,"},{"time":887911,"text":"invest in something new,"},{"time":889314,"text":"think that we can actually\nchange the route."},{"time":892432,"text":"I think we are doing this\nwith deforestation in Brazil,"},{"time":895454,"text":"and I hope we can do it also\nwith climate change in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898585,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899691,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}